item.name: Create an SPI at a point or update an existing SPI. If the video source is a UAV, and the UAV is also publishing its own position and SPI, those will be plotted on the map.

query.description: The length, in seconds, until the point will expire. Default is 300 seconds or 5 minutes.
Input parameter needed to update an existing SPI

The angular distance of the geoobject from the meridian of the Greenwich, UK, expressed in a positive or negative float (e.g -76.107.7998). Remember to set the display of your TAK in decimal coordinates, where West 77.08 is equal to '-77.08' in the API.
The angular distance of the geoobject from the Earth's equator, expressed in a positive or negative float (e.g 43.855682).
The UID of the connected drone
The name of the drone, which will also be the name of the video stream

response.name: Successfully created or updated the SPI
